    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and Related
        Components - Installation - Front Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s09.4.3" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Front Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The International &#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 is not equipped with a wear sleeve during factory
                    production. Wear sleeves are available with an oil seal service kit.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a 360&#176; bead of hydraulic sealant such as
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_200.xml" xrefid="s09.t3">Loctite&#174; 569</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s09.t3"/>
                or equivalent on leading edge of crankshaft before wear sleeve installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009033" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front oil seal and wear sleeve</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not separate wear sleeve from new oil seal; this damages seal.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_200.xml" xrefid="s09.t3">front seal/wear sleeve installer ZTSE4516</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s09.t3"/>, to drive oil seal and wear sleeve assembly into oil pump housing assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
